<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-80-1137 </DOCNO><TEXT>After a brief outline of the history of hydroelectric power in Mexico,the potential from this power source is estimated. The study was carriedout on a regional basis and classified into those which are planned orunder construction or operational. It is estimated that the potentialamounts to 159,624 GWh annual mean energy distributed in 570 projectsites. Finally, the expected growth of the system is shown under thecurrent 10 year plan. (U.K.).</TEXT></DOC>